cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DC

The paper discusses the efficiency and scalability of Multi Lane Capsule Networks (MLCN), which are a type of Deep Neural Network (DNN). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper focuses on image classification tasks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the use of parallel processing, which could place it in cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper proposes a reorganization of the Capsule Network, which is a type of DNN, indicating that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
